{{Quote|The interesting thing about the experience was that, even though I was a fan of the films, I found that there were a lot of people who were ''true'' aficionados, who knew everything down to the most minute detail. When I mentioned to some people that I was playing this character, they rattled off who Bail Organa is and who he is related to and the history of each of those people. I had to go to the ''Star Wars Encyclopedia'' to figure it all out.|Jimmy Smits|<ref name="mythmaking">''[[Mythmaking: Behind the Scenes of Attack of the Clones]]''</ref>}}
'''Jimmy Smits''' (born [[July 9]], [[1950s#1955|1955]])<ref name="SWYT 2020-07-09" /> is an actor who portrayed [[Senator]] [[Bail Prestor Organa|Bail Organa]] in [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'']] and [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|''Star Wars'': Episode III ''Revenge of the Sith'']] as well as in the [[Star Wars Legends|Legends]] [[Star Wars video games|video game]] ''[[Star Wars: The Force Unleashed]]''.<ref name="TFU">{{WebCite|url=http://www.theforce.net/latestnews/story/Jimmy_Smitts_In_The_Force_Unleashed_114753.asp|text=Jimmy Smitts In ''The Force Unleashed''!|date=2008-05-20|archivedate=20160414163644}}</ref> He also reprised his role as Senator Organa in the [[Star Wars Anthology Series|''Anthology'']] film ''[[Rogue One: A Star Wars Story]]''<ref name="Rogue One">{{WebCite|url=https://ew.com/article/2016/08/05/rogue-one-star-wars-jimmy-smits|text=''Rogue One: A Star Wars Story'': Jimmy Smits confirms he has a cameo|author=Robinson, Will|date=2016-08-05|work=Entertainment Weekly|archivedate=20191207155653}}</ref> and in the limited series ''[[Star Wars: Obi-Wan Kenobi]]''.<ref name="Part I">{{Kenobi|Part I}}</ref> [[Tony Gilroy]] and the team behind ''[[Star Wars: Andor]]'' worked hard to get Smits to return,<ref name="EW News">{{WebCite|url=https://ew.com/andor-creator-recasting-bail-organa-star-wars-benjamin-bratt-11721954|text=Andor creator explains recasting major Star Wars character with Benjamin Bratt|author=Dalton Ross|date=2024-04-29|work=''Entertainment Weekly''|archivedate=20250430013900}}</ref> but the actor was busy with another television project and thus, in the end, could not appear. As Gilroy believed that Organa needed to appear, he was recast and played by [[Benjamin Bratt]].<ref name="Collider News">{{WebCite|url=https://collider.com/andor-season-2-bail-organa-recast-benjamin-bratt-explained-tony-gilroy|text="You Have To Have Him": Tony Gilroy Reveals Why That 'Andor' Character Was Recast in Season 2|author=Rachel Leishman and Maggie Lovitt|date=2024-04-29|work=''Collider''|archivedate=20250430064431}}</ref>

